{"author":{"id":"27a92b445112509f896fbafb1295a63babb443b0af855b44b6dc09c14110e240"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1582298896,"nonce":"XAZVY0e3l5lpZWrmlHFeSVWJDS8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1NjkwMjI0MTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/337","origin":"github"},"title":"feat: graphql transaction","message":"Preliminary work at https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug/tree/graphql-transaction\n\nThe idea is to be able to\n1. open a transaction\n2. trigger a bunch of mutations (ex: comment+close)\n3. commit the transaction, rollback on error\n\nBenefits would be:\n- allow to deal with errors on commit in a single unit of changes and leave bugs in an untouched state\n- allow to deal with concurrent editing: the actual bug would not be changed until the transaction commit\n- allow to stack together multiple operations in the same git commit\n\nCode wise, the idea is, within the graphql server, attach the raw operation generated by a mutation in a list *per transaction* and apply it only on commit.","files":null}]}